Regex Exercises

to find all the words with “at” in them: /a[(^t$)]/gi
to find all the words that end in “s”: /[s$]\s/gim --OR-- /[s]\b/gim
to find all the consecutive vowels: /(ai)|(ae)|(ao)|(au)|(aa)|(ea)|(ei)|(ee)|(eo)|(eu)|(ia)|(ie)|(io)|(ii)|(iu)|(oa)|(oe)|(oi)|(oo)|(ou)|(ua)|(ue)|(ui)|(uo)|(uu)/gim --OR-- /\b\w*[aeiou]{2}\w*\b/gim [locates whole words]
ACTUALLY, that only finds 2 vowels; for two or more use: /[aeiou]{2,5}/gim
